There are no enemy ships in the Azov Sea.

In the Mediterranean there is one enemy ship - the carpet carrier "Caliber", a total volley of up to 8 rockets.

During the day in the interests of the Russian Federation, 19 ships passed the Kerch Strait to the Azov Sea, two of them moved from the Bosphorus Strait.

19 ships were passed to the Black Sea, 8 of them continued the movement in the direction of the Bosphorus.

"The Russian Federation continues to violate the International Convention on the Protection of Human Life at the Sea of 1974 (SOLAS), switching off automatic identification systems (AIS)," the Navy of the Armed Forces of Ukraine emphasized.
